- You are working on the OpsBrain monorepo. The actual app lives in `opsbrain/` (Vite + React).
- Prefer editing code under `opsbrain/src/**` unless the user explicitly asks otherwise.
- Prefer named exports; avoid default exports except for route-level pages/components already using defaults.
- Use early returns to reduce nesting.
- Never leave async operations without explicit loading/error states in the UI.
- For data fetching and caching, prefer `@tanstack/react-query` over ad-hoc `useEffect + useState` when touching or adding new flows.
- Always scope Supabase queries by `workspace_id` when the table is multi-tenant.
- When working with Supabase Realtime channels:
  - Attach `.on('postgres_changes', ...)` handlers before calling `.subscribe()`.
  - Always cleanup channels in `useEffect` cleanup to avoid duplicate subscriptions during HMR/StrictMode.
- Routing/auth:
  - `/app/*` must be protected; signed-out users must be redirected to `/Login`.
  - `/` should redirect to `/Login` when signed out and to `/app/Dashboard` when signed in.
- Keep components small: if a component grows beyond ~150–200 lines, extract subcomponents.
- Avoid `any` unless there is no viable alternative (prefer `unknown` + narrowing).
- Always run `npm run build` after meaningful changes; run `npm run lint` after refactors.
